  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of fiduciary duty while acting in a trusted capacity as an accountant. Embezzling $25,000 is a serious offense; however, several mitigating factors are present. The defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated remorse by initiating partial restitution. The courtroom outburst by the spectator was disregarded as it is not evidence and does not align with sentencing guidelines for a first-time non-violent white-collar offender. A sentence of 12 months reflects the gravity of the breach of trust while accounting for the defendant's rehabilitation efforts and lack of criminal record.",
  "verdict": 12
}
